
Lesson 2 lab; Using essential tools

1. locate the man page that shows how to set a password
A: man -k password | grep 1 (search failed) use man useradd and scroll to see related comamnds.
$sudo -   
$useradd anna
$passwd anna --> change password

2. Use the man page for useradd and as root, create a user with the name anna
A: $man passwd

3. set the password for user anna to "password"
A: $passwd anna
	prompt new password

4. use cd /etc to make etc your current directory

5. Use globbing and ls to show all files in etc/ that have a number in ther name
A: $ls -d *[0-9]*

6. Still from /etc, use the command ls -l. Use a pipe to display the results page by page. Next, type cd without any arguments
A: $ls -l | less

7. Use vim to create a file with the name users, and make sure that is contains the name Alex, Alexander, Linda and Belinda on separate lines.
A: $vim users
